#: 16_01P05
msgid "I'd like to withdraw the money in my account."
msgstr ""

#: 16_01P06
msgid "You have some interesting objects here."
msgstr ""

#: 16_01P07
msgid "I'm still intrigued by some of the interesting objects you have here."
msgstr ""

#: 16_01P08
msgid "Thanks. Goodbye."
msgstr ""

#: 16_02N01
msgid "Muy bien, señor. When will you be leaving?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_02P05
msgid "Easter Island."
msgstr ""

#: 16_02P06
msgid "Moka Moche."
msgstr ""

#: 16_03N01
msgid "Easter Island, a popular destination."
msgstr ""

#: 16_03N02
msgid "See, senor, an expedition led by Dr. Tweltrees has just returned there after several weeks."
msgstr ""

#: 16_03N03
msgid "Also, two Oriental gentlemen were inquiring only yesterday."
msgstr ""

#: 16_03N04
msgid "Si senor, you know them?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_03N05
msgid "When will you be leaving for Easter Island, Senor Ripley?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_03P02
msgid "Oh?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_03P03
msgid "Twelve trees? Again? The doctor gets around as much as I do."
msgstr ""

#: 16_03P04
msgid "One small, one big with glasses?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_03P05
msgid "Hmm, they are not on my Christmas list. This is getting to be a very small world indeed."
msgstr ""

#: 16_04N01
msgid "Moka Moche. It is very difficult to reach. Most tourists go to Machu Picchu. They are not interested in nameless civilizations no one has heard of before."
msgstr ""

#: 16_04N02
msgid "That would be Luis Arruno, señor. He was part of the expedition that discovered the lost city."
msgstr ""

#: 16_04N03
msgid "No problema, although he will not enter the city."
msgstr ""

#: 16_04N04
msgid "Ghosts, senor. Why else? When will you be leaving?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_04P02
msgid "I'm told there is a guide who knows mocha mocha. Luis something."
msgstr ""

#: 16_04P03
msgid "Could you arrange for him to guide me there?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_04P04
msgid "Why?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_05N01
msgid "It will go out on tomorrow's plane."
msgstr ""

#: 16_06N01
msgid "Pardon, senor Ripley, your account is empty."
msgstr ""

#: 16_07N01
msgid "Certainly, Senor Ripley. Please sign here."
msgstr ""

#: 16_08P01
msgid "NOW!"
msgstr ""

#: 16_08P02
msgid "I'll let you know."
msgstr ""

#: 16_09N01
msgid "Very good. Have a good trip, senor."
msgstr ""

#: 16_10N01
msgid "Perdonome, senor Ripley. Your account is empty. Will you be paying in cash?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_10N02
msgid "Mr. Ripley, lo siento. As I tell you, your account is empty. Would you prefer to pay in cash?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_11N01
msgid "Very good. Have a good trip, senor."
msgstr ""

#: 16_11P01
msgid "Of course, of course!"
msgstr ""

#: 16_12P01
msgid "I'd better change my money. I'll need escudos on Easter Island."
msgstr ""

#: 16_13N01
msgid "The mechanism has been with my family for many years. My grandfather had it custom made by one of the finest clockmakers in Switzerland. The original case fell to pieces long ago. I found that coral to replace it."
msgstr ""

#: 16_13N03
msgid "Well, the clock is old. The coral is not. I picked it up during a visit to... the seashore."
msgstr ""

#: 16_13N04
msgid "The ancient city of the snake, senor."
msgstr ""

#: 16_13N06
msgid "It is my son, Senor Ripley. Before he became ill, we would travel to the sea to watch the funny little birds. Now he must stay in bed. So I bring them to him. Our house is small and there are puffins everywhere, so some I keep here for decoration."
msgstr ""

#: 16_13N07
msgid "There is some improvement, senor."
msgstr ""

#: 16_13P01
msgid "This clock, may I ask where it came from?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_13P02
msgid "Where did you say the clock came from?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_13P03
msgid "I'm intrigued by that old clock there."
msgstr ""

#: 16_13P04
msgid "Where was that stellate found?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_13P05
msgid "Where did you say that Stelé was found?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_13P06
msgid "Someone here must like puffins."
msgstr ""

#: 16_13P07
msgid "How is your son, Matteo?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_14N01
msgid "Sí, señor. My grandfather used to say, people are always watching the clock. He wanted one that would look back."
msgstr ""

#: 16_14P01
msgid "Was the original also shaped like that?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_15N01
msgid "It is in God's hands."
msgstr ""

#: 16_15P01
msgid "Oh, I'm sorry to hear he's sick. What do the doctors say?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_16N02
msgid "Our house is small, and there are puffins everywhere, so some I keep here for decoration."
msgstr ""

#: 16_16P01
msgid "An unhappy visit?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_16P02
msgid "Ah, the puffins."
msgstr ""

#: 16_16P03
msgid "I'm sorry to hear your son sick. What did the doctors say?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_17N01
msgid "They are his most treasured possessions."
msgstr ""

#: 16_17P01
msgid "Ah, your son. I remember you said he was ill. How much he enjoyed those visits to the seashore, and the puffins."
msgstr ""

#: 16_18N01
msgid "No, Senor Ripley. I am sorry, but it is a family heirloom."
msgstr ""

#: 16_18N02
msgid "Lo siento mucho, señor, but where would I find such an unusual shape to replace it?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_18P01
msgid "Could I purchase your clock?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_18P02
msgid "How about just the choral, then?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_19P01
msgid "I'll keep my eyes open for something that might do just as well."
msgstr ""

#: 16_20P01
msgid "I recall seeing something on Easter Island at my work. Funny, now that I come to think of it, it was shaped like a puffin as well. Now, where was it?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_21N01
msgid "No problem, senor. When will you be leaving?"
msgstr ""

#: 16_22N01
msgid "They are his most treasured possessions."
msgstr ""

#: 16_22N02
msgid "Gracias, senor. It is in God's hands."
msgstr ""

#: 16_22P01
msgid "I'm glad to hear it. I remember you said how much you enjoyed those visits to the seashore, and the puffins."
msgstr ""

#: 16_22P02
msgid "I hope he recovers soon."
msgstr ""

#: 16_24P01
msgid "I'm ready to leave now."
msgstr ""

#: 16_27P01
msgid "Change my mind."
msgstr ""

#: 17_01N01
msgid "Would you hand me my shirt, please?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_01N02
msgid "Yes, would you hand me my shirt, please?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_01N03
msgid "How dare you sneak up on me like that?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_01N04
msgid "Many of the natives dress far more casually."
msgstr ""

#: 17_01N05
msgid "At a disadvantage, would you hand me my shirt, please?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_01P01
msgid "I am looking for Dr. Twelve Trees."
msgstr ""

#: 17_01P02
msgid "Are you part of the Twelve Trees Expedition?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_01P03
msgid "Whew! That's the most attractive pair of shoulders I've ever seen on an archaeologist."
msgstr ""

#: 17_01P04
msgid "Is that the standard kit these days for archaeologists?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_01P05
msgid "I'm Robert Ripley and you are..."
msgstr ""

#: 17_02P01
msgid "It was unintentional, madam. Miss, I assure you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_03P01
msgid "I'm liking Easter Island already."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04N02
msgid "Give me the shirt."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04N03
msgid "Swell."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04N04
msgid "May I help you?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_04N05
msgid "You were leering at Dr. Twelve Trees a moment ago."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04N06
msgid "I know who you are, Mr. Ripley. I recognized you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04N07
msgid "As far as I'm concerned, we share no common interests. I'm a scientist."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04N08
msgid "You're in..."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04N09
msgid "Was there something else?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_04N99
msgid "Showbiz."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04P01
msgid "Delighted!"
msgstr ""

#: 17_04P02
msgid "Uh, terribly sorry. Just be a moment."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04P06
msgid "Oh, really? That is to say, I wasn't leering. I'm Robert Ripley. I believe we share a common interest. I had some questions."
msgstr ""

#: 17_04P07
msgid "Ah!"
msgstr ""

#: 17_05N01
msgid "Master who?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_05N02
msgid "I was in thieves for a while. What stopped you?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_05N03
msgid "It's no secret."
msgstr ""

#: 17_05N04
msgid "Are you trying to be offensive?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_05N05
msgid "Now, if you have to ask, I have no answer for you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_05N06
msgid "Me too."
msgstr ""

#: 17_05N07
msgid "The woman who prays?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_05P01
msgid "We're both interested in Master Lu."
msgstr ""

#: 17_05P02
msgid "I tried to contact you in Egypt."
msgstr ""

#: 17_05P03
msgid "I understand you were in Peiping recently."
msgstr ""

#: 17_05P04
msgid "We both try to expand the world's knowledge."
msgstr ""

#: 17_05P05
msgid "What's wrong with showbiz?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_05P06
msgid "Sorry I bothered you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_05P07
msgid "Who is that old woman at the cove north of here?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_06N01
msgid "Hardly. I search for facts. You settle for the sensational."
msgstr ""

#: 17_06N02
msgid "Please."
msgstr ""

#: 17_06N03
msgid "What do you want, then?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_06P01
msgid "You don't find the comparison flattering, I take it."
msgstr ""

#: 17_06P02
msgid "All of my features are carefully documented."
msgstr ""

#: 17_06P03
msgid "Doctor, I don't want to quarrel with you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_07N01
msgid "Of what possible interest could an ancient sage have to the man who brought us an hourglass filled with jelly beans?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_07N02
msgid "Answer my question. Maybe then I'll answer yours."
msgstr ""

#: 17_07P01
msgid "Don't fence with me, doctor. You're supposed to be the leading Western authority on the man."
msgstr ""

#: 17_07P02
msgid "Ah, then you've been to the auditorium."
msgstr ""

#: 17_08N01
msgid "Master who?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_08P01
msgid "On the trail of Master Lu?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_09N01
msgid "What? But why would anyone..."
msgstr ""

#: 17_09N02
msgid "I'm a scientist, not a thief."
msgstr ""

#: 17_09N03
msgid "Why are you here, Mr. Ripley?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_09P01
msgid "Right after you visited the Hall of Classics, an attempt was made to steal a certain tablet of Master Luz."
msgstr ""

#: 17_09P02
msgid "Then you don't know anything about it?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_09P03
msgid "Someone might say archaeologists steal the past all the time. The British Museum is full of antiquities removed from their proper resting sites by scientists."
msgstr ""

#: 17_11N01
msgid "Then, why do it, Mr. Ripley?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_11N02
msgid "You already are. Please, come to the point."
msgstr ""

#: 17_11P01
msgid "Sorry to trouble you again."
msgstr ""

#: 17_11P02
msgid "I do need to talk to you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_12N01
msgid "RongoRongo tablets."
msgstr ""

#: 17_12N02
msgid "Yes, this is a fragile archaeological dig site. Please keep your hands and feet off."
msgstr ""

#: 17_12P01
msgid "May I ask why you went to see Master Lu's tablet at the Hall of Classics?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_12P02
msgid "Mind if I look around?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_13N01
msgid "RongoRongo tablets."
msgstr ""

#: 17_13P01
msgid "May I ask why you recently visited the Hall of Classics?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_14N01
msgid "There are sacred wood tablets found on this island. They've never been deciphered. I hope Lou's tablet might provide a clue to their translation."
msgstr ""

#: 17_14N02
msgid "There is definitely RongoRongo script on Lou's tablet, but it's intermingled with others. A translation is almost impossible. The islanders hid or buried most of their tablets generations ago. I was hoping to find some at the foot of this altar."
msgstr ""

#: 17_14N03
msgid "Mr. Ripley, you're a fast talker, I'll give you that. But I want some answers from you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_14P01
msgid "Take two and heartburn bubbles away."
msgstr ""

#: 17_14P02
msgid "And did it?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_14P03
msgid "I was wondering..."
msgstr ""

#: 17_16N04
msgid "I'll count the minutes."
msgstr ""

#: 17_16P01
msgid "I'm not sure I can trust you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_16P03
msgid "An attempt was made to steal Master Lu's tablet."
msgstr ""

#: 17_16P04
msgid "Maybe we should talk later."
msgstr ""

#: 17_17N02
msgid "Mr. Ripley, it wasn't necessary to track me halfway across the world to criticize my profession. Next time, write a letter."
msgstr ""

#: 17_17P01
msgid "Right after you saw it."
msgstr ""

#: 17_17P03
msgid "I need your help, but..."
msgstr ""

#: 17_19N01
msgid "It has nothing to do with me."
msgstr ""

#: 17_19P01
msgid "I was intercepted by two cutthroats who almost made an end of me in the desert."
msgstr ""

#: 17_19P02
msgid "I wish I could be sure of that."
msgstr ""

#: 17_20N01
msgid "I can tell."
msgstr ""

#: 17_20N02
msgid "How do I know you're not?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_20P02
msgid "How do I know you're not after the secrets of Master Lu for some sinister purpose?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_21N01
msgid "You're right. We do have something in common."
msgstr ""

#: 17_22N01
msgid "Oh."
msgstr ""

#: 17_22P01
msgid "There's something you should know."
msgstr ""

#: 17_23N01
msgid "Back so soon!"
msgstr ""

#: 17_23P01
msgid "Did you miss me?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_24N01
msgid "Really? I barely noticed you were gone."
msgstr ""

#: 17_24P01
msgid "Soon, I've been away for weeks."
msgstr ""

#: 17_25N01
msgid "Sounds as if you better decide whether you can trust me or not."
msgstr ""

#: 17_26N01
msgid "You made the right choice."
msgstr ""

#: 17_26N02
msgid "Well, then you're wasting my time. I have work to do."
msgstr ""

#: 17_26P01
msgid "Look, okay, I'll trust you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_26P02
msgid "I'm sorry, I can't risk it. There's too much at stake."
msgstr ""

#: 17_27N01
msgid "Mr. Ripley, no one has entered the tomb in over two thousand years. What makes you think you can succeed where generations before you have failed?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_27N02
msgid "It's such a crazy story. I almost believe you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_27N03
msgid "I'm not sure. I found a fragment of script on a stone head north of here, but I doubt it will be of much use to you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_27N04
msgid "This way."
msgstr ""

#: 17_27P01
msgid "Somebody, possibly the Japanese or the Nazis or the Chinese communists, it could even be Russians or mobsters for all I know, but somebody is after the first emperor's seal of office. I intend to beat them to it."
msgstr ""

#: 17_27P02
msgid "I don't know that I can. I only know I have to try. I'm the only person in a position to put all the pieces of Master Lu's puzzle together. I came here trying to find a clue to deciphering the Easter Island script on Lu's tablet, and to talk to you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_27P03
msgid "Crazy stories of my stock and trade. Can you help me?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_27P04
msgid "I'd like to see it."
msgstr ""

#: 17_28N01
msgid "It's about time. Why are you here?"
msgstr ""

#: 17_28P01
msgid "It looks like I have no choice. I have to trust you."
msgstr ""

#: 17_29N01
msgid "Suppose you tell me why you're here first."
msgstr ""

#: 17_29P01
msgid "Yes."
msgstr ""

#: 17_31N01
msgid "Yes, it is."
msgstr ""

#: 17_31P01
msgid "I was taking a look at the island. Beautiful place."
msgstr ""

#: 18_03N01
msgid "Did you learn anything?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_03N02
msgid "I'm sure if you can help that old woman she might be able to tell us something."
msgstr ""

#: 18_03N03
msgid "You haven't seen my poll, have you?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_03N04
msgid "I had it propped in the corner of the pit. I draped a tarp over it so I can work in the rain."
msgstr ""

#: 18_03P01
msgid "I'm back!"
msgstr ""

#: 18_03P02
msgid "Not much."
msgstr ""

#: 18_03P04
msgid "Uh, what, Paul?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_03P05
msgid "I'll keep my eyes open."
msgstr ""

#: 18_05N01
msgid "Any luck with the old woman?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_05N02
msgid "I beg your pardon?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_05N03
msgid "Hmm... pieces of obsidian used to create the pupils of the eyes came from a quarry to the west of here. Thanks to generations of thieves, I'm not sure what's left."
msgstr ""

#: 18_05P01
msgid "Hello!"
msgstr ""

#: 18_05P02
msgid "She insists that the watching god needs both eyes to see."
msgstr ""

#: 18_05P03
msgid "I've ridden the statue, now I need to find an eye."
msgstr ""

#: 18_07P01
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees."
msgstr ""

#: 18_09N01
msgid "That's terrific news! Did you learn anything from her?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_09P01
msgid "The watching god can see again. We also found the remains of the old woman's ancestor in a hole in the hillside beneath where the statue lay."
msgstr ""

#: 18_10N01
msgid "Why didn't you explore it?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_10N02
msgid "What kind of secret?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_10N03
msgid "I've already neglected my dig."
msgstr ""

#: 18_10P01
msgid "The hole where her ancestor was buried might be worth searching."
msgstr ""

#: 18_10P02
msgid "The old woman told me her ancestor knew a great secret."
msgstr ""

#: 18_10P03
msgid "Could you help me?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_11N01
msgid "I'll help."
msgstr ""

#: 18_11P01
msgid "I can't reach it on my own."
msgstr ""

#: 18_12N01
msgid "Show me!"
msgstr ""

#: 18_12P01
msgid "She was staring at the hole where we found his bones when she said it."
msgstr ""

#: 18_12P02
msgid "With pleasure."
msgstr ""

#: 18_13N01
msgid "Really?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_13P01
msgid "I have another hole for you to explore."
msgstr ""

#: 18_14N01
msgid "You know, I never found my pole. I know there's a lot of stealing on the island, but it was worthless."
msgstr ""

#: 18_14P02
msgid "I guess somebody found a use for it."
msgstr ""

#: 18_15N01
msgid "I seem to have lost my lighter. You haven't seen it, have you?"
msgstr ""

#: 18_15P02
msgid "Uh, gee, uh, no."
msgstr ""

#: 19_02N01
msgid "Only fragments. I'm hoping my exploration by the altar may produce something."
msgstr ""

#: 19_02N02
msgid "Mr. Ripley, I'm a trained archaeologist, and it's difficult enough for me."
msgstr ""

#: 19_02P01
msgid "Have you seen any other examples?"
msgstr ""

#: 19_02P02
msgid "I wonder if I could turn up some more."
msgstr ""

#: 19_03N01
msgid "I'll bet."
msgstr ""

#: 19_03N02
msgid "If you do find some more script, that will be payment enough."
msgstr ""

#: 19_03N03
msgid "There is someone you might want to talk to."
msgstr ""

#: 19_03P01
msgid "Well, I don't know. I have a way of stumbling over things other people pass by."
msgstr ""

#: 19_03P02
msgid "I'm very sorry about that. Please allow me to pay for the damage."
msgstr ""

#: 19_03P04
msgid "Who?"
msgstr ""

#: 19_04N01
msgid "Before you wander off, there is someone you might want to talk to."
msgstr ""

#: 19_05N01
msgid "An old woman who comes each day to a cove north of here to pray to the watchers."
msgstr ""

#: 19_05P02
msgid "Sounds like there's an interesting story attached to this old woman."
msgstr ""

#: 19_06N01
msgid "Remember the old woman you saw in the cove north of here?"
msgstr ""

#: 19_06P02
msgid "Yes, tell me about her."
msgstr ""

#: 19_07N01
msgid "Long ago, there were two tribes on the island, the Long Ears, who were the rulers, and the Short Ears, their subjects. The Long Ears ordered the Short Ears to build these famed Easter Island statues."
msgstr ""

#: 19_07N02
msgid "The long ears next order the short ears to clear the land of rocks and stones and throw them into the sea."
msgstr ""

#: 19_07N03
msgid "One theory states the long ears felt the other stones detracted from the majesty of the statues. But the short ears rebelled and determined to attack their oppressors."
msgstr ""

#: 19_07N04
msgid "There were two watchers. One, a man who kept an eye on the sea approach to the Long Ears lands and a guardian god who all believed would punish the Short Ears if he saw them pass."
msgstr ""

#: 19_07N99
msgid "A huge ditch stretched the width of the island and prevented attack by land. It was filled with wood and could be ignited to repel invaders. They knew they must attack from the sea. The watchers stood in their way. Come with me!"
msgstr ""

#: 19_07P02
msgid "A remarkable achievement."
msgstr ""

#: 19_07P03
msgid "Why?"
msgstr ""

#: 201M01
msgid "Yes, there's fear everywhere."
msgstr ""

#: 201M02
msgid "I will."
msgstr ""

#: 201M03
msgid "谢谢签书!"
msgstr ""

#: 201M04
msgid "Yes, we'll need travel permits to get to Xian province. I'll work on it."
msgstr ""

#: 201M06
msgid "It was impossible. The Japanese are everywhere. I suspect they want to be the first ones to open the tomb."
msgstr ""

#: 201M07
msgid "Xi'an province is outside their control, but once my mission was learned, I've been followed, and they are attempting to have our travel permits revoked."
msgstr ""

#: 201M08
msgid "But even if we can reach it, how will we get into the tomb?"
msgstr ""

#: 201M09
msgid "Yes, I have them. Here is the translation of the script you found in the temple. The Chinese was literal. I suppose so specific characters could be matched up next to their"
msgstr ""

#: 201R01
msgid "The city feels different than when we were last here, doesn't it?"
msgstr ""

#: 201R02
msgid "After we visit the Hall of Classics, go see your grandmother. Make sure she's okay."
msgstr ""

#: 201R03
msgid "Hello, Chien-Chu."
msgstr ""

#: 201R04
msgid "Any messages for me?"
msgstr ""

#: 201R05
msgid "Hmm... I sent a radiogram to Baron von Seltzim in New York that I was going after the Emerald Seal."
msgstr ""

#: 201R06
msgid "Hmm... I sent a radiogram to Baron von Seltzamp that I was going after the Emerald Seal."
msgstr ""

#: 201R07
msgid "All Posh Express offices look pretty much the same."
msgstr ""

#: 201R08
msgid "A classic vase in the Sung tradition. Good attempt, but I'm afraid it's a copy."
msgstr ""

#: 201R09
msgid "The Forbidden City, home to the Imperial Family. Peiping Opera, the Great Wall of China built by Xue Huangdi in only fifteen years. Jiananmen Square. Jiananmen means heavenly peace. May it always remain a haven of heavenly peace in the dark days to come."
msgstr ""

#: 201R10
msgid "From Auckland to Zanzibar, there's always a posh express office when you need it."
msgstr ""

#: 201R11
msgid "Beyond that rice paper is Peiping, a city of a thousand faces. Mysterious, exotic, and these days increasingly dangerous."
msgstr ""

#: 201R12
msgid "No time for reading!"
msgstr ""

#: 201R13
msgid "Jiang Shu knows Peiping and its environs better than any other man in China."
msgstr ""

#: 201R14
msgid "That rug may look authentic, but Jian Xu tells me it was made by some guy named Sam Glass in Manchester, England."
msgstr ""

#: 201R15
msgid "From everything I've seen since we landed, travel outside the city looks very difficult."
msgstr ""

#: 201R16
msgid "First stop, the Hall of Classics."
msgstr ""

#: 201R17
msgid "We need to find out as much about Master Lu as we can."
msgstr ""

#: 201R18
msgid "Mei, I'll leave the travel permits to you."
msgstr ""

#: 201R19
msgid "Ripley, you don't need a postcard."
msgstr ""

#: 201R20
msgid "I don't really need four-year-old copies of posh traveling."
msgstr ""

#: 201R21
msgid "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."
msgstr ""

#: 201R22
msgid "You don't need that."
msgstr ""

#: 201R23
msgid "This is no time to play the fool."
msgstr ""

#: 201R24
msgid "You can't do that."
msgstr ""

#: 201R25
msgid "I'd sketch the vase if it were authentic. It's not. And there's nothing else of interest to sketch in here."
