msgid "The medieval city of Danzig with its narrow winding streets. The Church of St. Mary. Langarten, spacious public gardens that rival the Tuileries of Paris. A beautiful city underappreciated by the common tourist."
msgstr ""

#: 401R10
msgid "Magnificent leathered windows. Shame they hide the view."
msgstr ""

#: 401R12
msgid "Horsed is a fine example of Posh Express courtesy and efficiency."
msgstr ""

#: 401R13
msgid "No time for revelry!"
msgstr ""

#: 401R22
msgid "A low railing separates the desk from the rest of the office."
msgstr ""

#: 401R23
msgid "Where horse can work with clients."
msgstr ""

#: 401R24
msgid "Where would we be without such modern appliances?"
msgstr ""

#: 401R25
msgid "For the life of me, I can't remember if I reminded my landlady to water the plants in my apartment."
msgstr ""

#: 401R29
msgid "I'd like to get a message to the Danzig Chief of Police. I'm curious to learn exactly how the last Baron von Seltsam died."
msgstr ""

#: 401R30
msgid "No, but certain events make the timing of the Baron's death troubling. Can you get a message to the Chief of Police?"
msgstr ""

#: 401R31
msgid "The baron's son hounded me about this as well. I can state, without hesitation, that the old baron died of pneumonia. The only curse on the old baron was a tendency to sleep with the windows open. Pleased to keep out of police affairs. Signed Krut, Chief of Police, Free City of Danzig."
msgstr ""

#: 401R31A
msgid "Pleased to keep out of police affairs. Signed Crutt, Chief of Police, Free City of Danzig."
msgstr ""

#: 401R32
msgid "Horst, I want to send a radiogram to Lima, Peru, to a professor Menendez at the university."
msgstr ""

#: 401R33
msgid "I also have a special parcel to send to New York."
msgstr ""

#: 401R34
msgid "Horst, I have a special parcel to send in New York."
msgstr ""

#: 401R35
msgid "A turtle of distinction, and I've packed lots of his favorite treats in with him for the long journey home. Handle with care."
msgstr ""

#: 401R36
msgid "Mr. Ripley Sir, thank you very much for returning Little Turtle Friend. Glad to report he arrived safely, although for some reason he not much like maple sugar treats anymore. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr ""

#: 401R37
msgid "Mr. Ripley, sir. Emerald, look nice, but act bad. Remind Feng Li of first wife. Feng Li thinks it must be cursed. After it on display only two hours, shark fall on one customer. Another customer have allergic reaction to puffball. Each day only get worse. I send back Emerald to you, sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr ""

#: 401R37A
msgid "After it on display only two hours, cow turntable motor break down. Shark fall on one customer. Another customer have allergic reaction to puffball. Each day only get worse. I send back Emerald to you sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr ""

#: 401R38
msgid "Mr. Ripley sir, no want emerald. Rocking man fall off chair. Customers get into fist fight. Almost squished tomato torso. Feng Li's eyebrows catch on fire. First time ever. I refuse delivery if you send emerald to me again. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr ""

#: 401R39
msgid "Refuse delivery. Feng Li warned me that's what he'd do."
msgstr ""

#: 401R40
msgid "I can catch a taxi to the castle."
msgstr ""

#: 401R41
msgid "The coat rack has been put to its proper use."
msgstr ""

#: 401X01
msgid "Herr Ripley, it is good to see you again."
msgstr ""

#: 401X02
msgid "There is a message for you."
msgstr ""

#: 401X03
msgid "There are messages for you."
msgstr ""

#: 401X04
msgid "Oh, indeed, my hair. It is a local attraction."
msgstr ""

#: 401X05
msgid "There is a taxi stand in the next block."
msgstr ""

#: 401X06
msgid "I'm sorry, Hare Ripley, but no, he belonged to my uncle, France. He drained every drop on the first night of Oktoberfest, twelve years ago."
msgstr ""

#: 401X07
msgid "It is difficult to say. I will ask him when he comes out of the coma."
msgstr ""

#: 401X08
msgid "Good day, Mr. Ripley."
msgstr ""

#: 401X09
msgid "You suspect foul play?"
msgstr ""

#: 401X10
msgid "Leave it to me, Herr Ripley."
msgstr ""

#: 401X11
msgid "They're good here, Ripley."
msgstr ""

#: 401X12
msgid "SPECIAL?"
msgstr ""

#: 401X13
msgid "Auf jeden Fall, Herr Ripley."
msgstr ""

#: 402R01
msgid "Hello, my name is Ripley."
msgstr ""

#: 402R02
msgid "And this, I take it, is Ace of Spades Castle."
msgstr ""

#: 402R03
msgid "I'm no common tourist."
msgstr ""

#: 402R04
msgid "Sorry to bother you."
msgstr ""

#: 402R05
msgid "I don't mean to be a pest."
msgstr ""

#: 402R06
msgid "Just one more thing..."
msgstr ""

#: 402R07
msgid "Sorry."
msgstr ""

#: 402R08
msgid "Magnificent castle! I'll bet there's a story behind the reoccurring motif."
msgstr ""

#: 402R09
msgid "It's shaped like the Ace of Spades."
msgstr ""

#: 402R10
msgid "Beautifully tended flower bed."
msgstr ""

#: 402R11
msgid "There is a persistent architectural theme about this castle."
msgstr ""

#: 402R12
msgid "That man is one of the only things I've seen around here not shaped like the Ace of Spades."
msgstr ""

#: 402R13
msgid "Even casual conversation with Wolf could put a serious dent in my bank account."
msgstr ""

#: 402R14
msgid "The ironwork of the gate is shaped like the ace of spades."
msgstr ""

#: 402R15
msgid "The old wheelbarrow is not shaped like the Ace of Spades."
msgstr ""

#: 402R16
msgid "I'd better not meddle with the topiary, especially while he's wielding those shears."
msgstr ""

#: 402R17
msgid "It's a nice wheelbarrow, but I really don't have much use for it."
msgstr ""

#: 402R18
msgid "The topiary is firmly rooted in the ground."
msgstr ""

#: 402R28
msgid "Mr. Robert Ripley to see the Barrett."
msgstr ""

#: 402R29
msgid "Hello again."
msgstr ""

#: 402R30
msgid "Magnificent castle! If a bit one-note for my taste."
msgstr ""

#: 402R31
msgid "It's Robert Ripley again."
msgstr ""

#: 402R32
msgid "NOPE!"
msgstr ""

#: 402W01
msgid "I am called Wolf."
msgstr ""

#: 402W02
msgid "Your powers of observation do you credit, Mein Herr, but the castle to the tourist is not open. I'm sorry."
msgstr ""

#: 402W03
msgid "I'm a busy man, please let me work."
msgstr ""

#: 402W04
msgid "I have no time for endless conversation."
msgstr ""

#: 402W05
msgid "Find someone else to answer your questions."
msgstr ""

#: 402W06
msgid "My hair, my job is difficult enough. If you steal my tools, it will be impossible."
msgstr ""

#: 402W07
msgid "Danke, mein Herr. A man can never have too much small change."
msgstr ""

#: 402W08
msgid "Do I look like the Rothschild's bank? I have no use for foreign currency."
msgstr ""

#: 402W09
msgid "Yeah?"
msgstr ""

#: 402W10
msgid "Herr Ripley! The bell! I thought it might be you!"
msgstr ""

#: 402W11
msgid "God in Himmel! The old baron!"
msgstr ""

#: 403R01
msgid "The old baron is dead?"
msgstr ""

#: 403R02
msgid "When did he die?"
msgstr ""

#: 403R03
msgid "February. Not long after Otto wrote me the letter. He mentions in it he was ill."
msgstr ""

#: 403R04
msgid "This graveyard would not be out of place in the works of Poe or that new fellow Lovecraft."
msgstr ""

#: 403R05
msgid "That tomb is certainly impressive."
msgstr ""

#: 403R05A
msgid "What's that in the corner? A bell?"
msgstr ""

#: 403R06
msgid "A ventilation opening."
msgstr ""

#: 403R06A
msgid "I remember reading that they are necessary to disperse certain gases."
msgstr ""

#: 403R07
msgid "A tomb with a doorbell? That can't be customary."
msgstr ""

#: 403R08
msgid "Sturdy stone urns filled with dirt."
msgstr ""

#: 403R09
msgid "That's quite a stone wall."
msgstr ""

#: 403R09A
msgid "I wonder why it was built so high? To keep someone out or to keep something in?"
msgstr ""

#: 403R10
msgid "Someone's left a ladder leaning against the tomb."
msgstr ""

#: 403R11
msgid "Here lies an atheist, all dressed up and no place to go."
msgstr ""

#: 403R12
msgid "I promise never to marry again, Jacob."
msgstr ""

#: 403R13
msgid "Beneath the stone, a lump of clay, lies the man called Peter Hannels, who early in the month of May, took off his winter flannels."
msgstr ""

#: 403R14
msgid "Let the stone bear this headline. The writer below met one last deadline."
msgstr ""

#: 403R15
msgid "Here lies Lotta Dust."
msgstr ""

#: 403R16
msgid "Here lies the body of Gretel Sprechtestunnel, who pleased many a man and never vexed one, unlike the woman under the next stone."
msgstr ""

#: 403R17
msgid "This stone was raised by Frieda's lord, not Frieda's virtues to record, for they are known to all the town. This stone was raised to keep her down."
msgstr ""

#: 403R18
msgid "His foot is slipped and he did fall. Help, help! he cried. And that was all."
msgstr ""

#: 403R19
msgid "Here lies the body of Erika Bent. She kicked up her heels and away she went."
msgstr ""

#: 403R20
msgid "Stephen and Time are now both even. Stephen beat Time, now Time beat Stephen."
msgstr ""

#: 403R21
msgid "Here lies a poor toss tennis ball, racketed from spring to fall."
msgstr ""

#: 403R22
msgid "At rest beneath this slab of stone lies Stingy Verner Viatt. He died one morning just at ten and saved a dinner by it."
msgstr ""

#: 403R23
msgid "Here lies Yohan Yeast. Pardon me for not rising."
msgstr ""

#: 403R24
msgid "Here lies the body of Heinrich Blake, stepped on the gas instead of the brake."
msgstr ""

#: 403R25
msgid "I started out in life with the idea that the world had an opening for me... and it did."
msgstr ""

#: 403R26
msgid "It was a cough that carried him off. It was a coffin they carried him off in."
msgstr ""

#: 403R27
msgid "...sacred to the memory of Rolf Baumgartner, who died August 6, 1800. His widow, aged 24, lives at 7 Lindenstrasse and possesses every qualification for a good wife."
msgstr ""

#: 403R28
msgid "The urns are filled with dirt and far too heavy."
msgstr ""

#: 403R29
msgid "All I can really see from this angle is that wooden beam that runs the length of the tomb and a rope hanging down next to it."
msgstr ""

#: 403R30
msgid "I can't reach the bell."
msgstr ""

#: 403R31
msgid "I'll need something less unwieldy to ring the bell."
msgstr ""

#: 403R32
msgid "I don't need the ladder to climb over the wall. There's a perfectly good gate."
msgstr ""

#: 403R33
msgid "It would be more seemly to simply sketch the epitaphs."
msgstr ""

#: 403R41
msgid "The epitaphs on the tombstones might provide enough material for more than one cartoon."
msgstr ""

#: 403R42
msgid "I've already sketched the best epitaphs."
msgstr ""

#: 403R43
msgid "Sorry to bother you."
msgstr ""

#: 403R44
msgid "I don't mean to be a pest."
msgstr ""

#: 403R45
msgid "Just one more thing..."
msgstr ""

#: 403R46
msgid "That must belong to the gardener."
msgstr ""

#: 403R47
msgid "Sorry."
msgstr ""

#: 403R48
msgid "Ripley, you have more important things to do than tease an old man."
msgstr ""

#: 403R49
msgid "I'll put one treat on the beam and save the rest for a rainy day."
msgstr ""

#: 403R50
msgid "He just sits there like a turtle."
msgstr ""

#: 403R51
msgid "Wow! Aided in one gulp! Little fella sure loves those things!"
msgstr ""

#: 403R52
msgid "I've already got a turtle treat."
msgstr ""

#: 403R53
msgid "The Gardener's Edger."
msgstr ""

#: 403R54
msgid "The shovel isn't quite long enough to reach the bell."
msgstr ""

#: 403R55
msgid "A tomb with a doorbell. That's one for Ripley."
msgstr ""

#: 403W01
msgid "Otto, the sixth Baron von Celtsam, mein Herr."
msgstr ""

#: 403W02
msgid "Your powers of observation continue to amaze me."
msgstr ""

#: 403W03
msgid "February. The Baron's son Albert has inherited the title."
msgstr ""

#: 403W04
msgid "Just so."
msgstr ""

#: 403W05
msgid "I'm a busy man, please let me work."
msgstr ""

#: 403W06
msgid "I have no time for endless conversation."
msgstr ""

#: 403W07
msgid "Find someone else to answer your questions."
msgstr ""

#: 403W08
msgid "Please do not touch my hair."
msgstr ""

#: 403W09
msgid "Danke, mein Herr. A man can never have too much small change."
msgstr ""

#: 403W11
msgid "Do not meddle with the bell, mein Herr. It is disrespectful to the old Baron."
msgstr ""

#: 403W12
msgid "Yeah, you should be."
msgstr ""

#: 403W13
msgid "You again! I should have guessed."
msgstr ""

#: 403W14
msgid "NO RESPECT!"
msgstr ""

#: 403W15
msgid "What? Have you nothing better to do?"
msgstr ""

#: 403W16
msgid "I am an old man, Mein Herr. Please! I have enough work to tire me without running here because of your foolishness!"
msgstr ""

#: 403W17
msgid "This must stop. I will tell the Baron when he returns. He will not be allowed to set foot on the grounds again."
msgstr ""

#: 403W18
msgid "You have escaped from the asylum! Play your games! Ring it all you like! I will not come running here again!"
msgstr ""

#: 404R01
msgid "I have a letter from his father. It's quite urgent."
msgstr ""

#: 404R02
msgid "I have a letter from his father. It's quite urgent."
msgstr ""

#: 404R03
msgid "I have a letter from him."
msgstr ""

#: 404R04
msgid "No, it's signed AUTO."
msgstr ""

#: 404R05
msgid "Not long after he wrote me the letter, he mentions in it he was ill. I'm sorry."
msgstr ""

#: 404R06
msgid "Maybe I better see the sun, then. It's quite urgent."
msgstr ""

#: 404R07
msgid "The castle's entry is immense. I wonder how they clear the cobwebs."
msgstr ""

#: 404R08
msgid "The section of wall the door is set into is an ace of spades."
msgstr ""

#: 404R08A
msgid "The section of wall the door to the billiards room is set into is an ace of spades."
msgstr ""

#: 404R09
msgid "The section of wall the door to the sitting room is set into is an ace of spades."
msgstr ""

#: 404R10
msgid "The section of wall the door is set into is not an ace of spades, but there are spades carved into it."
msgstr ""

#: 404R11
msgid "The section of wall that massive door is set into is an ace of spades."
msgstr ""

#: 404R12
msgid "The motif is tiresomely familiar."
msgstr ""

#: 404R13
msgid "A former Baron von Seltsam, no doubt."
msgstr ""

#: 404R14
msgid "An old and dusty portrait. Another von Seltsam, I suspect."
msgstr ""

#: 404R15
msgid "Ripley, you're a guest in this castle. It would be impolite to insist."
msgstr ""

#: 404R16
msgid "Can you think of anything else that might help me?"
msgstr ""

#: 404R17
msgid "Any ideas where I should look next?"
msgstr ""

#: 404R18
msgid "Any old stories you haven't told me?"
msgstr ""

#: 404R19
msgid "Anything else about the old baron I should know?"
msgstr ""

#: 404R20
msgid "What happened to Wolf? I don't see him anywhere."
msgstr ""

#: 404R21
msgid "I'm sorry."
msgstr ""

#: 404R22
msgid "Um... right."
msgstr ""

#: 404R23
msgid "Sorry."
msgstr ""

#: 404R30
msgid "The man is the picture of a trusted family retainer."
msgstr ""

#: 404R30A
msgid "The brass work on the door strikes a familiar note."
msgstr ""

#: 404U01
msgid "From Mr. Albert, mein Herr?"
msgstr ""

#: 404U02
msgid "Ah, that would be the old Baron mine here. He died in February, I'm afraid."
msgstr ""

#: 404U03
msgid "As are we all, my dear. The old baron was well loved, as is his son."
msgstr ""

#: 404U04
msgid "Please do wait in the sitting room, mein Herr."
msgstr ""

#: 404U05
msgid "I'm sorry, Mein Herr. Into that part of the castle you may not go."
msgstr ""

#: 404U06
msgid "Nein."
msgstr ""

#: 404U07
msgid "I am sorry."
msgstr ""

#: 404U08
msgid "I have told you all I know."
msgstr ""

#: 404U09
msgid "I know nothing else."
msgstr ""

#: 404U10
msgid "The gardener is gone, mein Herr. A bell rang from within the old baron's tomb. It was a false alarm, of course. The old fool didn't realize it and ran off somewhere. And now I'm having difficulty replacing him. The villagers are so superstitious, you know."
msgstr ""

#: 404U11
msgid "It is not your fault."
msgstr ""

#: 404U12
msgid "Hey Ripley, I happened to look into the billiards room just now. I saw you take one of the balls. Pleased to leave the ball where you found it?"
msgstr ""

#: 404U13
msgid "Hey Ripley, I cannot allow you to leave with Sir Barron's property. Please to put the ball back."
msgstr ""

#: 405B01
msgid "Mr. Ripley, Von Seltsam."
msgstr ""

#: 405B01A
msgid "Please, forgive the tennis togs. The third set was more of a struggle than I expected."
msgstr ""

#: 405B02
msgid "You knew my father, I believe."
msgstr ""

#: 405B03
msgid "Indeed. This house alone is testament to that."
msgstr ""

#: 405B04
msgid "Ah, you're that Mr. Ripley. I am also a fan."
msgstr ""

#: 405B05
msgid "The first emperor of China, Master Lu."
msgstr ""

#: 405B05A
msgid "As you might have gathered, my father was an orientalist of some note. It's a pity he died before he was able to pursue this line of research. It sounds fascinating."
msgstr ""

#: 405R01
msgid "I never had the pleasure of meeting him, I'm afraid. By all accounts, he was quite a fellow."
msgstr ""

#: 405R02
msgid "He wrote me this shortly before he died."
msgstr ""

#: 405R03
msgid "Thank you."
msgstr ""

#: 405R04
msgid "Castles were designed to make you feel small."
msgstr ""

#: 405R05
msgid "Shaped like the Ace of Spades. How quaint."
msgstr ""

#: 405R06
msgid "If there wasn't an ace of spades in the windows, I would have been disappointed."
msgstr ""

#: 405R07
msgid "Even animals cooperate with the Baron's unique decorating scheme."
msgstr ""

#: 405R08
msgid "What would the wall of a castle be without some poor decapitated beast hung on it?"
msgstr ""

#: 405R09
msgid "The Baron's coat of arms contains the Ace of Spades. Who would have guessed?"
msgstr ""

#: 405R10
msgid "They would need chandeliers that big to light this room at night."
msgstr ""

#: 405R11
msgid "An impressive collection of books in many languages. Most of them appear to be science texts or about the Orient."
msgstr ""

#: 405R12
msgid "The sofa looks comfortable enough to sleep on."
msgstr ""

#: 405R13
msgid "The chairs and sofa constitute an island of comfort in this cold room."
msgstr ""

#: 405R14
msgid "A library table. There's a journal here written by the young baron."
msgstr ""

#: 405R14A
msgid "Hmm. Notes on the latest racing cars, clippings of the tennis tournament he won. Oh, nothing here concerning the old Baron, unfortunately."
msgstr ""

#: 405R15
msgid "The sofa looks comfortable enough to sleep on. There seems to be something sticking out from underneath it."
msgstr ""

#: 405R16
msgid "You need thick rugs like that to temper the cold of the castle's floors."
msgstr ""

#: 405R17
msgid "It looks like money."
msgstr ""

#: 405R18
msgid "While it would make a nice companion for my cow with a spot shaped like Ireland, the Baron has explained it must remain in the castle. I'll respect his wishes."
msgstr ""

#: 405R19
msgid "I suppose you could say someone has already taken the deer's head. Unfortunately, that's not much of an oddity."
msgstr ""

#: 405R20
msgid "They're bolted to the wall. Medieval weapons don't do me much good anyway."
msgstr ""

#: 405R21
msgid "I'd love to spend time browsing through the baron's library. Maybe when I have more time, I'll ask him if I might."
msgstr ""

#: 405R22
msgid "The furniture is more comfortable to sit on than to lug around."
msgstr ""

#: 405R23
msgid "The Baron needs his journal to recount his adventures in the world of sport."
msgstr ""

#: 405R24
msgid "Goodness gracious, it's a fifty million mark note. Unfortunately, today it's as worthless as Confederate currency. I'm told doctors used these during the Great War as prescription blanks."
msgstr ""

#: 405R30
msgid "The brass work on the door strikes a familiar note."
msgstr ""

#: 405R31
msgid "If the baron wants the door closed, I'm sure he'll have his butler do it."
msgstr ""

#: 406R01
msgid "So the Baron believes the curse of the Romanov Emerald taints this room. It all looks pretty harmless to me."
msgstr ""

#: 406R02
msgid "The billiard table is a beauty. I used to play a little 8 ball myself when I was a lad."
msgstr ""

#: 406R03
msgid "A darkboard cabinet, just like the one at my favorite pub on Second Avenue."
msgstr ""

#: 406R04
msgid "The lamp illuminates every corner of the billiard table."
msgstr ""

#: 406R05
msgid "Everything necessary for a challenging game of Billiards."
msgstr ""

#: 406R06
msgid "The cabinet is closed."
msgstr ""

#: 406R07
msgid "Golly!"
msgstr ""

#: 406R07A
msgid "Maybe the room is unlucky after all."
msgstr ""

#: 406R08
msgid "That Ace of Spades looks slightly different than the rest of the wallpaper design."
msgstr ""

#: 406R09
msgid "The old baron's writing desk. Some books, and a piece of paper. None of any use, I'm afraid."
msgstr ""

#: 406R09A
msgid "The old baron's writing desk."
msgstr ""

#: 406R10
msgid "A red billiard ball. Luckily for anyone wanting to play, it is not shaped like the ace of spades."
msgstr ""

#: 406R11
msgid "A table with a lamp on it."
msgstr ""

#: 406R12
msgid "An uncomfortable looking chair of hard wood."
msgstr ""

#: 406R13
msgid "The person in that portrait looks familiar."
msgstr ""

#: 406R14
msgid "A few papers referring to household matters."
msgstr ""

#: 406R15
msgid "Great Caesar's Ghost! It's addressed to me!"
msgstr ""

#: 406R16
msgid "I wonder what those keys unlock."
msgstr ""

#: 406R17
msgid "The papers won't help me, I'm afraid."
msgstr ""

#: 406R18
msgid "Mr. Ripley, this interesting item came into my possession quite by accident last year while I was in China. I thought it might amuse you. To the best of my knowledge, it is the cheapest stamp ever struck, worth but four thousandths of one of your American pennies. Please accept it with my compliments. I look forward to meeting you in person soon to plan our great adventure tackling the mysteries of the First Emperor's tomb. Signed Otto, 6 Baron von Seltzer."
msgstr ""

#: 406R18A
msgid "To the best of my knowledge, it is the cheapest stamp ever struck, worth but four thousandths of one of your American pennies. Please accept it with my compliments."
msgstr ""

#: 406R18B
msgid "I look forward to meeting you in person soon to plan our great adventure tackling the mysteries of the First Emperor's tomb. Signed Otto, 6th Baron von Celtsam."
msgstr ""

#: 406R18C
msgid "Mr. Ripley, this interesting item came into my possession quite by accident last year while I was in China. I thought it might amuse you. To the best of my knowledge, it is the cheapest stamp ever struck, worth but four thousandths of one of your American pennies. Please accept it with my compliments. I look forward to meeting you in person soon to plan our great adventure tackling the mysteries of the First Emperor's tomb. Signed Otto, 6th Baron von Seltsam. I would have enjoyed seeing this thing through with you, Baron. I'm sorry it wasn't meant to be."
msgstr ""

#: 406R19
msgid "Worth only a fraction of a cent! How wonderful!"
msgstr ""

#: 406R20
msgid "LOCKED."
msgstr ""

#: 406R21
msgid "I wonder what's in there."
msgstr ""

#: 406R23
msgid "The Ace of Spades is missing from this deck of cards."
msgstr ""

#: 406R23A
msgid "Must be where that card on the wall came from."
msgstr ""

#: 406R24
msgid "The deck is incomplete, useless for playing games."
msgstr ""

#: 406R25
msgid "Parcheesi, Mahjong, Chinese checkers, and that new game, Monopoly."
msgstr ""

#: 406R25A
msgid "It's rather fun. I wonder if it will catch on."
msgstr ""

#: 406R26
msgid "None of the keys fit. Well, I didn't have time for darts anyway."
msgstr ""

#: 406R27
msgid "None of the keys fit. I prefer pocket billiards myself."
msgstr ""

#: 406R28
msgid "Curious. The table suddenly seems to be on an angle."
msgstr ""

#: 406R29
msgid "I do believe a red ball has been added to the rack. That must be the ball I put into the slot."
msgstr ""

#: 406R30
msgid "Stairs. Baron, you're a wily old coot, but I think I'm on to you."
msgstr ""

#: 406R40
msgid "The curse of the Romanov Emerald should no longer haunt this room. It should make playing games in here a bit more fun."
msgstr ""

#: 406R41
msgid "Your secret is safe with me, Baron."
msgstr ""

#: 406R42
msgid "So a ball dropped into the hole in the smoking hutch pops out there. Ingenious!"
msgstr ""

#: 406R43
msgid "Seven years, bad luck!"
msgstr ""

#: 406R44
msgid "That Ace of Spades conceals the switch to the old Baron's smoking hatch."
msgstr ""

#: 406R44A
msgid "That Ace of Spades conceals the switch."
msgstr ""

#: 406R45
msgid "I know I've seen that face somewhere before."
msgstr ""

#: 406R46
msgid "That useless deck of 51 cards is in there."
msgstr ""

#: 406R47
msgid "There's a drawer in the games cabinet."
msgstr ""

#: 406R48
msgid "There's a drawer in the writing desk."
msgstr ""

#: 406R49
msgid "A vertical rack of billiard balls with a hole at the top."
msgstr ""

#: 406R50
msgid "A two-button switch. Fascinating."
msgstr ""

#: 407R01
msgid "The Baron's private laboratory. Other than the Baron, I may well be the only other living soul ever to enter this room."
msgstr ""

#: 407R02
msgid "Shut tight. I have a sneaking suspicion it's not going to be as easy to get out of here as it was to get in."
msgstr ""

#: 407R03
msgid "I wonder what experiments that eccentric old gentleman conducted at this table."
msgstr ""

#: 407R04
msgid "There's a drawer in the work table."
msgstr ""

#: 407R05
msgid "The sink has been stained with countless chemicals."
msgstr ""

#: 407R06
msgid "A rubber plug."
msgstr ""

#: 407R07
msgid "A faucet."
msgstr ""

#: 407R08
msgid "The Fawcett Handle."
msgstr ""

#: 407R09
msgid "It's some sort of pivot bolted to the tabletop."
msgstr ""

#: 407R10
msgid "There are two brass nozzles protruding through the tabletop."
msgstr ""

#: 407R11
msgid "A piston is set into the table. Beneath the table, tubing runs from the piston to one of two brass nozzles. A second tube runs up through the table to an axle of some sort. The axle is attached to a large gear."
