msgstr ""

#: 607R15
msgid "I'm a better cartoonist than I am a sculptor."
msgstr ""

#: 608O01
msgid "One eye is missing."
msgstr ""

#: 608O02
msgid "There is only one watching God, and it must have two eyes before it can see."
msgstr ""

#: 608O03
msgid "If you have something to say to me..."
msgstr ""

#: 608O04
msgid "I pray..."
msgstr ""

#: 608O05
msgid "Privacy."
msgstr ""

#: 608O06
msgid "Is this all?"
msgstr ""

#: 608O07
msgid "This I is not complete."
msgstr ""

#: 608O08
msgid "Find the missing part. Then the watching god will see again."
msgstr ""

#: 608O09
msgid "Yes! Yes! Now the watching god will see again!"
msgstr ""

#: 608O09A
msgid "You are taller. Your deeds make you so."
msgstr ""

#: 608O10
msgid "Place your hands on the watching god."
msgstr ""

#: 608O11
msgid "Spread your legs!"
msgstr ""

#: 608O12
msgid "Come here."
msgstr ""

#: 608O13
msgid "Place your hands on the hill."
msgstr ""

#: 608O14
msgid "There is something up there. I saw it when I replaced the eye."
msgstr ""

#: 608O15
msgid "The bones of the grandfather of my grandfathers. He did not run away in fear. The short ears pushed the watching god on top of him. I will give his bones the rest they deserve, and all will honor him."
msgstr ""

#: 608O15A
msgid "The watching gods cease again, and my family's honor is restored. You are the one from my vision. May you find what you seek on Easter Island."
msgstr ""

#: 608O16
msgid "The grandfather of my grandfathers was the keeper of a great secret."
msgstr ""

#: 608O17
msgid "You again."
msgstr ""

#: 608O18
msgid "You can make the watching gods see again?"
msgstr ""

#: 608O19
msgid "Huuh!"
msgstr ""

#: 608R01
msgid "What happened to him?"
msgstr ""

#: 608R02
msgid "Fascinating!"
msgstr ""

#: 608R03
msgid "Thanks, doctor."
msgstr ""

#: 608R04
msgid "I won't disturb her prayers again unless I find a way to help her."
msgstr ""

#: 608R04A
msgid "I won't disturb her prayers unless I find a way to help her."
msgstr ""

#: 608R05
msgid "Hard for the watching God to see with its face buried in the hillside like that."
msgstr ""

#: 608R06
msgid "That stone looks like it's been wedged under the base of the statue."
msgstr ""

#: 608R07
msgid "The statue obviously stood on that base, facing the sea."
msgstr ""

#: 608R08
msgid "Lava. Long ago this mountain must have been an active volcano."
msgstr ""

#: 608R09
msgid "Lots of crevices and holes in the lava."
msgstr ""

#: 608R10
msgid "That hole is much larger than the others."
msgstr ""

#: 608R11
msgid "Eons ago, this ravine provided a natural path for lava flowing to the sea."
msgstr ""

#: 608R12
msgid "Reminds me of one of those comical birds, puffins."
msgstr ""

#: 608R12A
msgid "Shame there's a piece missing. It might make an interesting exhibit in the auditorium."
msgstr ""

#: 608R13
msgid "That stump is practically petrified."
msgstr ""

#: 608R14
msgid "She looks as if she's squatted here all her life, buffeted by the elements, growing old, but never swerving from her vigilant faith in her ancestor."
msgstr ""

#: 608R14A
msgid "Even if she can't help me, it would give me a great deal of satisfaction to end her vigil."
msgstr ""

#: 608R14B
msgid "The old woman has never lost her faith."
msgstr ""

#: 608R15
msgid "The watching god can see again."
msgstr ""

#: 608R16
msgid "Lots of people can see with one eye."
msgstr ""

#: 608R17
msgid "Oh, this is going to be harder than I thought."
msgstr ""

#: 608R18
msgid "It's now wedged beneath several tons of statues."
msgstr ""

#: 608R19
msgid "Without a block and tackle to move the statue, that stump is staying where it is."
msgstr ""

#: 608R20
msgid "I can use Easter Island as the subject of one of my cartoons."
msgstr ""

#: 608R21
msgid "I already have a sketch of Easter Island."
msgstr ""

#: 608R22
msgid "I don't know how the Easter Islanders toted these statues around, but I have no way of transporting the head."
msgstr ""

#: 608R31
msgid "May I talk to you for a moment?"
msgstr ""

#: 608R32
msgid "Tell me about yourself."
msgstr ""

#: 608R33
msgid "What do you pray for?"
msgstr ""

#: 608R34
msgid "I wonder who she is."
msgstr ""

#: 608R35
msgid "I'd better not disturb her prayers again until I learn more about her."
msgstr ""

#: 608R35A
msgid "I'd better not disturb her prayers until I learn more about her."
msgstr ""

#: 608R36
msgid "The statue's face is buried in the hillside."
msgstr ""

#: 608R37
msgid "I suspect there is an interesting story behind her being here."
msgstr ""

#: 608R38
msgid "The watching god is facing the ocean, but according to the old woman, it still needs a second eye to see."
msgstr ""

#: 608R39
msgid "That stone was used to keep the statue's face lodged against the hillside."
msgstr ""

#: 608R40
msgid "The stump fills the hole."
msgstr ""

#: 608R41
msgid "That petrified stump is pinned by the pole."
msgstr ""

#: 608R42
msgid "I'm afraid Dr. Twelve Trees won't be getting her pull back."
msgstr ""

#: 608R43
msgid "Well, yes."
msgstr ""

#: 608R44
msgid "I'm an adventurer, not an optician."
msgstr ""

#: 608R45
msgid "At long last, I may be able to help her."
msgstr ""

#: 608R46
msgid "Why? Thank you!"
msgstr ""

#: 608R47
msgid "Ah, some sort of arcane ritual. Dr. Twelve-Tree should see this."
msgstr ""

#: 608R48
msgid "Madame, I must be out of shape. Your feather-like form is beginning to tell on me, I'm afraid."
msgstr ""

#: 608R49
msgid "And spread my legs."
msgstr ""

#: 608R50
msgid "Can you help me? I'm looking for Easter Island artifacts."
msgstr ""

#: 608R51
msgid "A great secret, eh? I wonder what you meant by that."
msgstr ""

#: 608R51A
msgid "A great secret, eh?"
msgstr ""

#: 608R52
msgid "The watching God can see once more."
msgstr ""

#: 608R53
msgid "Oh, does it?"
msgstr ""

#: 608R53A
msgid "The watcher's body was in a hole up there."
msgstr ""

#: 608R54
msgid "Now, why didn't I think of that?"
msgstr ""

#: 608R55
msgid "See anything, doctor?"
msgstr ""

#: 608R56
msgid "Uh, sorry!"
msgstr ""

#: 608R57
msgid "Well, not usually, doctor. Uh, uh, no."
msgstr ""

#: 608R58
msgid "What are they?"
msgstr ""

#: 608R59
msgid "Gosh, what a find."
msgstr ""

#: 608R60
msgid "I'm not sure why."
msgstr ""

#: 608R61
msgid "The good doctor dropped her lighter."
msgstr ""

#: 608R62
msgid "The old woman's ancestor took several secrets to his grave. A horn, and some sort of navigation chart, or maybe simply a map."
msgstr ""

#: 608R62A
msgid "The old woman's ancestor took several secrets to his grave."
msgstr ""

#: 608R63
msgid "The stone is far too heavy to shift."
msgstr ""

#: 608R64
msgid "I could fill the horn with water, but it would run right out again."
msgstr ""

#: 608R65
msgid "I now have a horn full of water."
msgstr ""

#: 608R66
msgid "Doctor, twelve trees lighter. She dropped it during our unfortunate tumble."
msgstr ""

#: 608R67
msgid "Madam, excuse me."
msgstr ""

#: 608R68
msgid "I'm pretty sure I have what you need."
msgstr ""

#: 608R69
msgid "I won't disturb her prayers again unless I find a way to help her."
msgstr ""

#: 608R70
msgid "Madam, I have what you need."
msgstr ""

#: 608R71
msgid "Yes!"
msgstr ""

#: 608R72
msgid "It's full to the brim."
msgstr ""

#: 608R73
msgid "The sea is quite calm in this protected cove."
msgstr ""

#: 608R74
msgid "I'll have to move the pole first."
msgstr ""

#: 608R75
msgid "The pole is resting on the stone."
msgstr ""

#: 608R76
msgid "The driftwood stump is wedged into the hole."
msgstr ""

#: 608R77
msgid "Hitting the statue with the pole won't accomplish anything."
msgstr ""

#: 608T01
msgid "The night of the attack, the short ears toppled the statue face down so that they could pass without the gods seeing them."
msgstr ""

#: 608T01A
msgid "There she is. Supposedly a descendant of the original Watcher."
msgstr ""

#: 608T02
msgid "He vanished. Some say he ran away in fear when the short ears approached. But the old woman refuses to believe her ancestor was a coward. She comes here every day to pray to the watching God. She believes, if it can be made to see again, all will know the truth of that night."
msgstr ""

#: 608T03
msgid "I have long suspected that she knows more than she'll say. Some family tradition, perhaps, that could help both of us in our quests. Good luck, Mr. Ripley. I have to get back to my dig."
msgstr ""

#: 608T04
msgid "How did you ever manage to shift that statue?"
msgstr ""

#: 608T05
msgid "Hey, that looks like my pole!"
msgstr ""

#: 608T06
msgid "I have a great idea. You stand against the hill and give me a boost up."
msgstr ""

#: 608T07
msgid "Wait a second!"
msgstr ""

#: 608T08
msgid "There... there's something here, all right."
msgstr ""

#: 608T09
msgid "Mr. Ripley, do you continually tear off the clothes of every woman you meet?"
msgstr ""

#: 608T10
msgid "Sticks, a red stone, a scallop shell, a starfish, a shark's tooth and a seahorse all tied with grass, and a horn made from wheelbone."
msgstr ""

#: 608T11
msgid "The horn might be of interest to you, but it's too recent for me. Not more than four or five hundred years old. As for the other, I've seen something like it before. The islanders used them as navigation charts. That redstone in the center comes from the quarry. Not of much archaeological significance, unfortunately."
msgstr ""

#: 608T11A
msgid "Hmm, looks like a dead end. I have to get back to my dig."
msgstr ""

#: 608T12
msgid "Will you be staying on Easter Island much longer, Mr. Ripley?"
msgstr ""

#: 608T13
msgid "If you are, I'd better send for a trunk of new clothes."
msgstr ""

#: 610K01
msgid "It's hot here. I can't stand heat."
msgstr ""

#: 610K02
msgid "I don't like to sweat. Peasants sweat. I am not a peasant."
msgstr ""

#: 610K03
msgid "She's not paying attention, Shen Gao. I'm insulted."
msgstr ""

#: 610K04
msgid "This could be so simple. You tell us where Mr. Ripley is, you tell us what he has learned, you win a prize. We give you your life. What could be simpler than that?"
msgstr ""

#: 610K05
msgid "You may hit her, yes."
msgstr ""

#: 610K06
msgid "You will answer my questions, doctor. The only uncertainty in the entire process is how much pain you must endure first."
msgstr ""

#: 610K07
msgid "Where is Mr. Ripley?"
msgstr ""

#: 610K08
msgid "Why did Mr. Ripley come to Easter Island?"
msgstr ""

#: 610K09
msgid "What has Mr. Ripley learned?"
msgstr ""

#: 610K10
msgid "Does Mr. Ripley know Master Lu visited here?"
msgstr ""

#: 610K11
msgid "Did you find anything that might help decipher Lou's tablet?"
msgstr ""

#: 610K12
msgid "You may hit her, Shen Gao."
msgstr ""

#: 610K13
msgid "Now, we begin again."
msgstr ""

#: 610K14
msgid "Mr. Ripley, how nice of you to join us. Now we will learn what we need to know."
msgstr ""

#: 610R01
msgid "Looks like the beasts have roughed her up pretty good."
msgstr ""

#: 610R02
msgid "Nasty piece of work."
msgstr ""

#: 610R03
msgid "From the looks of them, wrestling those ruffians into submission is not an option."
msgstr ""

#: 610R04
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees Hut"
msgstr ""

#: 610R05
msgid "The excavation."
msgstr ""

#: 610R06
msgid "The generator shed."
msgstr ""

#: 610R07
msgid "I wonder if that window is locked."
msgstr ""

#: 610R08
msgid "The electrical power cable."
msgstr ""

#: 610R09
msgid "The cliff rises over thirty feet above the sea."
msgstr ""

#: 610R10
msgid "Just walking up to them may not have been an idea worthy of Tom Swift."
msgstr ""

#: 610R11
msgid "Somehow, I don't think they are in the mood for musical accompaniment."
msgstr ""

#: 610R12
msgid "Beating up a defenseless woman? So that's your game, is it?"
msgstr ""

#: 610R13
msgid "Sometimes the truth hurts."
msgstr ""

#: 610R14
msgid "Doctor Twelve Trees, may I be of any assistance?"
msgstr ""

#: 610R15
msgid "Maybe I could have been of more assistance alive."
msgstr ""

#: 610R16
msgid "Ripley, for heaven's sakes, getting yourself killed won't help Dr. Twelve Trees."
msgstr ""

#: 610R17
msgid "Looks like I'm out of time... and out of luck."
msgstr ""

#: 610R18
msgid "Now is not the time for drawing pictures."
msgstr ""

#: 610R20
msgid "How would that help?"
msgstr ""

#: 610S01
msgid "Now..."
msgstr ""

#: 610T01
msgid "You. If you think I'm going to tell you anything."
msgstr ""

#: 615R01
msgid "Doctor, are you okay?"
msgstr ""

#: 615R02
msgid "Oh, uh, fine, uh..."
msgstr ""

#: 615R02A
msgid "I'm Robert."
msgstr ""

#: 615R03
msgid "I've crossed paths with them before. They're working for whoever is after the seal. I'm very sorry you got stuck in the middle of this."
msgstr ""

#: 615R04
msgid "Maybe you can. I think I've found something. What do you make of it?"
msgstr ""

#: 615R05
msgid "Uh, no, that's what I was asking."
msgstr ""

#: 615R06
msgid "And that stick?"
msgstr ""

#: 615R07
msgid "Uh, what is Samantha?"
msgstr ""

#: 615R08
msgid "Ah, well, gosh, good!"
msgstr ""

#: 615R09
msgid "The symbols you recognize, where did you see them before?"
msgstr ""

#: 615R10
msgid "Doctor, uh, Samantha, thank you."
msgstr ""

#: 615R11
msgid "You may have the stick to aid your research."
msgstr ""

#: 615R12
msgid "I'd better make a sketch of these glyphs. You may have the stick to aid your research."
msgstr ""

#: 615R13
msgid "Oh, here is your spark plug tool. I, uh, borrowed it."
msgstr ""

#: 615R14
msgid "Yes, with these glyphs I'm one step farther on my quest, but the end isn't in sight yet."
msgstr ""

#: 615R15
msgid "Maybe we will."
msgstr ""

#: 615T01
msgid "Mr. Ripley, after saving my life, you've earned the right to call me Samantha."
msgstr ""

#: 615T02
msgid "Yes, you are."
msgstr ""

#: 615T03
msgid "But who were they?"
msgstr ""

#: 615T04
msgid "I misjudged you, Robert. The fate of the world may rest in your hands. I wish I could do more to help."
msgstr ""

#: 615T05
msgid "Huh, a rongo-rongo, definitely, but... Robert, do you know what this is?"
msgstr ""

#: 615T06
msgid "Centuries ago, Dutch slavers carried off the last of the islanders who could read and write. Before they did, one of the islanders must have tried to record the language so that later generations could relearn it."
msgstr ""

#: 615T07
msgid "These pictures are not writing. They are all the same, but each set contains one more picture than the last. It's obvious, Robert!"
msgstr ""

#: 615T08
msgid "They are numbers. One or first, two or second, and so on."
msgstr ""

#: 615T08A
msgid "The stick you found, we can at last begin a translation."
msgstr ""

#: 615T09
msgid "On Master Lu's tablet."
msgstr ""

#: 615T10
msgid "Under the circumstances, I won't complain."
msgstr ""

#: 615T10A
msgid "You... you have to go now, don't you?"
msgstr ""

#: 615T11
msgid "Well, good luck. Maybe we'll run into each other again in some forgotten corner of the world someday."
msgstr ""

#: 623R01
msgid "The stone used to fashion the top knots of the statues."
msgstr ""

#: 623R02
msgid "One of Easter Island's famed statues."
msgstr ""

#: 623R03
msgid "The quarry is littered with great chunks of stone."
msgstr ""

#: 623R04
msgid "A patch of clay."
msgstr ""

#: 623R05
msgid "Mist clings to the cool walls of the quarry, resisting the hot sun overhead."
msgstr ""

#: 625R01
msgid "There's a starfish carved into the rock."
msgstr ""

#: 626R01
msgid "There's a seahorse carved into the rock."
msgstr ""

#: 644R01
msgid "There's a scallop carved into the rock."
msgstr ""

#: 651R01
msgid "There's a shark's tooth carved into the rock."
msgstr ""

#: 701R01
msgid "Good day!"
msgstr ""

#: 701R02
msgid "My name is Robert Ripley."
msgstr ""

#: 701R03
msgid "I'm on the trail of a very elusive Chinese gentleman called Master Lu."
msgstr ""

#: 701R04
msgid "No, but I believe he passed through here some 21 centuries ago."
msgstr ""

#: 701R05
msgid "Is there anyone here I can talk to who knows the history of this place?"
msgstr ""

#: 701R06
msgid "Can you direct me to the temple?"
msgstr ""

#: 701R07
msgid "Many thanks, uh..."
msgstr ""

#: 701R08
msgid "Thanks, Terenjit."
msgstr ""

#: 701R10
msgid "That's an unusual looking skin. Polar bear?"
msgstr ""

#: 701R11
msgid "Yeti? The abominable snowman of the Himalayas? Would you be interested in selling it?"
msgstr ""

#: 701R12
msgid "No kidding."
msgstr ""

#: 701R13
msgid "A genuine Yeti skin hanging in a travel office. Unlikely."
msgstr ""

#: 701R14
msgid "Scenes from the top of the world. The Chumbi Valley. Mount Kachinjunga, nearly as tall as Everest. Sherpas. Monasteries perched on the sides of cliffs. Even tropical scenes from the south. A fascinating region."
msgstr ""

#: 701R15
msgid "Authentic prayer wheels of the Himalayas."
msgstr ""

#: 701R17
msgid "The Himalayas. Is there a more majestic and mysterious mountain range on this planet?"
msgstr ""

#: 701R19
msgid "A genuine Sikkimese prayer wheel."
msgstr ""

#: 701R20
msgid "A bright looking young man, as you'd expect from Posh Express."
msgstr ""

#: 701R21
msgid "One brochure on prayer wheels should be enough for any traveler."
msgstr ""

#: 701R24
msgid "The Yeti skin, if that's what it is, belongs to Posh Express."
msgstr ""

#: 701R25
msgid "The prayer wheel contains a prayer to protect travelers."
msgstr ""

#: 701R35
msgid "A sketch of a Yeti skin would be even more difficult to believe than the skin itself, and there is nothing else of interest to sketch here."
msgstr ""

#: 701R36
msgid "I'd rather buy that unusual looking skin if there is a story behind it, and there is nothing else of interest to sketch here."
msgstr ""

#: 701R37
msgid "Hello, Taranjeet."
msgstr ""

#: 701R38
msgid "I'd like to send a message to an associate of mine in Peiping. Her name is Mei Chen."
msgstr ""

#: 701R39
msgid "Dear Robert, with the help of scholars from the Imperial School, I have translated the early Chinese characters you sent me. They agree that the Chinese is a translation of the ancient Sikkimese script on the palm frond you found in the temple. I'll give you the translation when I see you next."
msgstr ""

#: 701R39A
msgid "It's good I'm staying with my grandmother. I can look after her, while I try to secure our travel permits. But Peiping is becoming a very frightening place, little resembling the fine city I remember as a child. If I don't see you when you return to Peiping, it's only because I'm spending almost every waking hour in government offices, trying to get our permits. I miss you with all my heart, May."
msgstr ""

#: 701R40
msgid "Taranjeet is an extremely helpful young man."
msgstr ""

#: 701R41
msgid "For the life of me, I can't remember if I reminded my landlady to water the plants in my apartment."
msgstr ""

#: 701R42
msgid "May will be able to find someone to translate the ancient Chinese characters from the temple."
msgstr ""

#: 701X01
msgid "Sat Sri Akal, Sahib. How may I assist you?"
msgstr ""

#: 701X02
msgid "Ah, Mr. Ripley, there is a message for you."
msgstr ""

#: 701X02A
msgid "There is a message for you."
msgstr ""

#: 701X03
msgid "Ah, Mr. Ripley, there are messages for you."
msgstr ""

#: 701X03A
msgid "There are messages for you."
msgstr ""

#: 701X04
msgid "Does this gentleman reside in Sakim, sahib?"
msgstr ""

#: 701X05
msgid "Twenty-one centuries? I have not had the honor of working here that long."
msgstr ""

#: 701X06
msgid "There are holy men at a temple near the village where I was born. It is said that they were here before all others."
msgstr ""

#: 701X07
msgid "Certainly, sahib."
msgstr ""

#: 701X07A
msgid "This road will take you to the Temple of the Hidden Way."
msgstr ""

#: 701X08
msgid "Terenjit sahib."
msgstr ""

#: 701X09
msgid "Yeti sahib."
msgstr ""

#: 701X10
msgid "No, Sahib, they are very rare."
msgstr ""

#: 701X11
msgid "Sat Sri Akal, Mr. Ripley."
msgstr ""

#: 702G01
msgid "You are a member of the temple!"
msgstr ""

#: 702G02
msgid "Forgive me, I was prepared to bar your way."
msgstr ""

#: 702G03
msgid "We all must be vigilant, especially after last week. You may pass!"
msgstr ""

#: 702G04
msgid "I understand. We all must question every day if we ever hope to find true enlightenment."
msgstr ""

#: 702G05
msgid "How may I serve you?"
msgstr ""

#: 702G06
msgid "Questions can reveal the hidden way."
msgstr ""

#: 702G07
msgid "Questioning, seeking, only by these may we find the hidden way."
msgstr ""

#: 702G08
msgid "Only he who asks will learn."
msgstr ""

#: 702G09
msgid "The right question is worth a thousand wrong ones."
msgstr ""

#: 702G10
msgid "We all must help each other in our quests."
msgstr ""

#: 702G11
msgid "Questions are but steps on the path to true enlightenment."
msgstr ""

#: 702G12
msgid "We believe in the testing of the faithful."
msgstr ""

#: 702G13
msgid "We believe only through questioning can we find answers to that which puzzles us."
msgstr ""

#: 702G14
msgid "We believe that to learn one must study."
msgstr ""

#: 702G15
msgid "We believe one may not reach true enlightenment until one has found the hidden way."
msgstr ""

#: 702G16
msgid "We do not believe in trial and error."
msgstr ""

#: 702G17
msgid "We believe in method and reason."
msgstr ""

#: 702G18
msgid "We believe anyone who proves himself worthy by throwing off the trappings of the outer world may join us."
msgstr ""

#: 702G19
msgid "We welcome questers from all lands."
msgstr ""

#: 702G20
msgid "Only those of the temple may pass."
msgstr ""

#: 702R01
msgid "The Temple of the Hidden Way crowns a mountaintop in a remote corner of the Himalayas."
msgstr ""

#: 702R01A
msgid "Some Buddhist influence in its construction, yet it's unlike anything I've ever seen."
msgstr ""

#: 702R02
msgid "While there are similarities to other temples in this part of the world, the temple of the hidden way is unique. The origins of the sect which resides here are lost in the mists of time."
msgstr ""

#: 702R03
msgid "Those within guard their privacy well."
msgstr ""

#: 702R04
msgid "The only way to reach the temple is through that ornate gateway, but I don't see a welcome map."
msgstr ""

#: 702R05
msgid "Wherever there is a gate, there is always a guard. This one is a substantial looking fellow with the gleam of a zealot in his eye."
msgstr ""

#: 702R05A
msgid "Hope he speaks English."
msgstr ""

#: 702R05B
msgid "Wherever there is a gate, there is always a guard."
msgstr ""

#: 702R06
msgid "I confess I was testing your vigilance, my friend."
msgstr ""

#: 702R07
msgid "As you see, I am a member of the temple."
msgstr ""

#: 702R08
msgid "Here's something that might interest you."
msgstr ""

#: 702R09
msgid "Uh... yes, I am."
msgstr ""

#: 702R10
msgid "Your vigilance is commendable."
msgstr ""

#: 702R11
msgid "Don't be surprised if I ask further questions."
msgstr ""

#: 702R12
msgid "Sorry to bother you again."
msgstr ""

#: 702R13
msgid "I had a couple more questions."
msgstr ""

#: 702R14
msgid "I've returned!"
msgstr ""

#: 702R15
msgid "I came all the way back here because I wanted to ask you some more questions."
msgstr ""

#: 702R16
msgid "Can you tell me more about the temple?"
msgstr ""

#: 702R17
msgid "I'd like to hear what those of the temple believe."
msgstr ""

#: 702R18
msgid "If an outsider were interested in the sect, what would you tell him?"
msgstr ""

#: 702R19
msgid "Can you tell me some key doctrines of the Temple of the Hidden Way?"
msgstr ""

#: 702R20
msgid "Numerous Westerners are fascinated by Eastern religion. What would you tell them about your beliefs?"
msgstr ""

#: 702R21
msgid "I'm not going to insult the guard by trying to bribe him."
msgstr ""

#: 702R32
msgid "The only access to the temple is through this gateway."
msgstr ""

#: 703A01
msgid "The wise man bends the rope others might cut."
msgstr ""

#: 703B01
msgid "Every creature has its purpose. It is better to catch a snake than to slay it."
msgstr ""

#: 703C01
msgid "He who attracts unwanted attention must find that which excites his spectator more."
msgstr ""

#: 703D01
msgid "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."
msgstr ""

#: 703D02
msgid "You are correct. I seek wisdom. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."
msgstr ""

#: 703R01
msgid "The temple of the hidden way was crafted with stone and a hunger for knowledge."
msgstr ""

#: 703R02
msgid "A prayer wheel."
msgstr ""

#: 703R03
msgid "I'm looking for the path to enlightenment. Can you help me?"
msgstr ""

#: 703R04
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for grace."
msgstr ""

#: 703R05
msgid "The wheel is fixed in place."
msgstr ""

#: 703R06
msgid "I can't budget."
msgstr ""

#: 703R07
msgid "Guess this isn't one of the five I need to move."
msgstr ""

#: 703R08
msgid "There's already a prayer wheel in place."
msgstr ""

#: 703R09
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for stillness."
msgstr ""

#: 703R10
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for love."
msgstr ""

#: 703R11
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for serenity."
msgstr ""

#: 703R12
msgid "There's the prayer wheel of wisdom."
msgstr ""

#: 703R13
msgid "The guard would never let me take any of the temple's prayer wheels. I'd better put them back."
msgstr ""

#: 704E01
msgid "The slowest of creatures may still walk farther than a man."
msgstr ""

#: 704F01
msgid "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."
msgstr ""

